Sprint Goal:
Finalize all our documentation, polish the multimedia assets, and also preapre for the project presentation. Furthermore, we need to ensure all wireframes are final and the report is in development.

Sprint Duration:
Mid-week 3 - Week 4

Tasks Selected:
1.Final review of all diagram - Class, Use Case, and Wireframes, ensuring it meets all the user requirements
2.Prepare final presentation and report

Work Completed:
All design assets are all now finalized at this point and are put in the desing folder in GitHub. The presentation preparation was also done during this period.

Challenges:
Having to present a reasonably large project in 12 minutes was found as a challenge because we had a lot of wireframes to deal with.

Sprint 3 Retrospective
What went well:
The project was completed within the due date and was satisfied with the UI design.

